								<h2>Who am I<br />
								</h2>
								<p>
									
									I am part of <font color="">FICO</font>'s analytic team, working on the Falcon project.
									Falcon is a platform that helps financial institutions to detect and prevent fraud seamlessly, in real time,
									all while advancing the consumer experience.
									The secret receipt we use is a combination of deep learning techniques, behavioral analytics,
									and a focus on the interpretability of the resulting model.<br /><br />
									
									Before joining FICO I have been a post-doctoral fellow for CMS collaboration,
									one of the 2 main experiments at the Large Hadron Collider (LHC) at CERN.
									I directed several groups and activities related to the data acquisition and data analysis aimed
									to estimate detector conditions for on-line data-taking, data reconstruction, and data simulation.
									Also, I developed and coordinate data analysis targeting the search for extremely rare processes 
									hidden in the PB of data through deep learning algorithms, and advanced statistical analysis.<br /><br />

									I truly enjoy learning. <br />
									I also love combat sports, technology, magic, and traveling.<br /><br />
								</p>
							</header>
